1. Download and install vagrant from https://www.vagrantup.com/
2. Create a directory and copy the files Vagrantfile and twister.sh into 
that directory; if you are behind a proxy server, edit twister.sh to
set the username, password and proxy server
3. Run 'vagrant up'
4. Once vagrant is up, open browser on host machine and go to
http://127.0.0.1:8080
5. Java security settings must be edited to add exception
 for http://127.0.0.1:8080 site
6. Connect to Tiwster with username 'user' and password 'password'
7. Select 'Test execution'
8. Ignore ( press OK ) the warnings
9. Use the default project when you are prompted to select a project file
10. Now you have a project opened, to run press 'Run' button
11. To stop Twister virtual machine, run 'vagrant destroy'; Other options to
 stop the machine, please read vagrant documentation
